doc.previous: New Jersey is the birthplace of modern inventions such as: FM radio, the motion picture camera, the lithium battery, the light bulb, transistors, and the electric train. Other New Jersey creations include: the drive-in movie, the cultivated blueberry, cranberry sauce, the postcard, the boardwalk, the zipper, the phonograph, saltwater taffy, the dirigible, the seedless watermelon,[157] the first use of a submarine in warfare, and the ice cream cone.[158]
doc.after: There are mineral museums in Franklin and Ogdensburg.
